But in fact, these two works just look similar.

249
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:17,360
As the original creator, I hope to get legal recognition.

250
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:21,120
Ms. Ruan, I'm sorry. I'm a lawyer, not your PR team.

251
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,233
I can't support your literary ideals.

252
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:29,140
Got it.

253
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:36,260
<i>Ms. Ruan. Just a friendly reminder.</i>

254
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:39,799
<i>I don't think any lawyer will take your advice.</i>

255
00:21:49,019 --> 00:21:51,300
<i>How did it go with Lawyer Fan?</i>

256
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:57,439
<i>Lawyer Fan heard my request and almost showed me the door.</i>

257
00:21:57,439 --> 00:22:01,759
<i>But doing it my way might indeed be a thankless task.</i>

258
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,499
Hello, Lawyer Liu.

259
00:22:13,499 --> 00:22:15,560
Ruan Yu.

260
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:19,180
I'm calling to ask if you've made up your mind.

261
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:21,420
<i>Are you really not going to sue?</i>

262
00:22:21,420 --> 00:22:26,300
Lawyer Liu, how do you see my case being handled?

263
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:30,519
Proving the outline was stolen is the easiest way.

264
00:22:32,220 --> 00:22:35,299
<i>What's wrong?</i>Did you run into some trouble?

265
00:22:35,299 --> 00:22:38,800
You can talk to me. Even if I'm not your lawyer,

266
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:41,300
<i>aren't we still friends?</i>

267
00:22:42,655 --> 00:22:46,120
I was wondering if I could prove

268
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,560
the originality of my work in this case.

269
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:51,200
Well, actually...

270
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,960
It's okay, Lawyer Liu. I understand.

271
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,760
You could.

272
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,680
I could?

273
00:23:04,066 --> 00:23:08,180
Lawyer Liu, if you're doing this
as a favor to a friend, don't force yourself.

274
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:09,879
- I know it's--
- Of course not.

275
00:23:09,879 --> 00:23:12,100
I'm not forcing myself.

276
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:14,379
Not at all.

277
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:20,280
Are you on speakerphone over there, Lawyer Liu?

278
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:21,440
Yes.

279
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:24,099
Sorry about that, Ruan Yu. Excuse me for a moment.

280
00:23:24,099 --> 00:23:26,180
I have to sign two documents.

281
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:27,900
<i>Okay!</i>

282
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:34,900
What are your instructions?

283
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:55,675
"Proving your originality isn't essential,

284
00:23:55,675 --> 00:23:58,146
but as supporting evidence,

285
00:23:58,733 --> 00:24:01,679
it could have a positive impact on the outcome of the case.

286
00:24:01,679 --> 00:24:05,499
This request is feasible."

287
00:24:05,499 --> 00:24:08,920
Aren't you worried, though, that the comparison might not go well?

288
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:13,106
Hold on.

289
00:24:13,106 --> 00:24:15,980
I need to sign two more documents.

290
00:24:17,306 --> 00:24:18,906
Okay!

291
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:25,799
In China, for cases like this, the simplest way

292
00:24:25,799 --> 00:24:28,179
is to start with the theft of the outline.

293
00:24:28,179 --> 00:24:30,540
That's different from how things work abroad.

294
00:24:30,540 --> 00:24:33,440
In any country, you have to start with the outline theft.

295
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:36,026
Haven't we been saying...

296
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:40,579
What if the outline wasn't stolen at all?

297
00:24:40,579 --> 00:24:42,699
What do you mean?

298
00:24:42,699 --> 00:24:44,420
<i>Lawyer Liu, are you still there?</i>

299
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:46,219
If you're busy,

300
00:24:46,219 --> 00:24:48,926
we can talk later.

301
00:24:49,739 --> 00:24:53,160
Hurry up.
I don't have that many documents to sign.

302
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:05,200
"Regardless of how the comparison turns out,

303
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:11,440
I believe a truly original work is worth taking a shot like this."

304
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,079
Really?

305
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:16,400
Thank you so much, Lawyer Liu.

306
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:22,719
You're welcome. Goodbye.

307
00:25:29,405 --> 00:25:30,940
You can't handle the case like this.

308
00:25:30,940 --> 00:25:34,060
Aren't you just forcing a sale on her?

309
00:25:34,060 --> 00:25:38,223
So many firms in Hang City. Why make her choose Zhikun Law Firm?

310
00:25:38,223 --> 00:25:42,220
Because for this case, only I know how to win it.

311
00:25:43,459 --> 00:25:45,973
"Only I know how to win it."

312
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:51,919
Don't tell me it's because of me.

313
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:55,920
Why go through all this trouble?

314
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:58,433
You could have just told me directly.

315
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:03,053
But come to think of it, Ruan Yu

316
00:26:03,053 --> 00:26:07,780
is definitely the best
among all the blind dates I've had over the years.

317
00:26:07,780 --> 00:26:12,880
She's pretty, well-educated, and a writer.

318
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:15,839
I'm a lawyer.

319
00:26:15,839 --> 00:26:18,933
A writer and a lawyer.

320
00:26:19,860 --> 00:26:22,760
It'd be a lovely story if word got out.

321
00:26:22,760 --> 00:26:24,420
Alright.

322
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:27,600
Then I'll just wait and see
in which episode you two get together.

323
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,444
You've watched too many dramas.

324
00:26:29,444 --> 00:26:31,520
- Grab dinner together tonight?
- I'll pass.

325
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:33,380
Where are you going then?

326
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,500
Su City.

327
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:42,580
Fine, I'll eat with someone else.

328
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:45,380
A work meeting turns into a date.

329
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:53,580
Ms. Ruan, see you tonight.

330
00:26:57,380 --> 00:27:01,280
A lawyer and a writer. It'd be a lovely story.

331
00:27:01,986 --> 00:27:03,879
It does have a nice ring to it.

332
00:27:03,879 --> 00:27:06,340
Song, you're back!

333
00:27:06,340 --> 00:27:08,880
When did you get back?

334
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,973
Did you come back because of that thing?

335
00:27:14,940 --> 00:27:17,105
Fine, don't answer me then.

336
00:27:17,105 --> 00:27:20,300
Song, come home for dinner tonight!

337
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:22,080
I'm eating out.

338
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:24,980
<i>Come on!</i>

339
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:28,340
Mom really missed you.

340
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:31,840
I'll pick you up after school.<i>We'll go to that place you sent me.</i>

341
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:34,580
Okay, okay! It's a deal.

342
00:27:34,580 --> 00:27:37,500
See you after school. Love you!

343
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:44,659
What a coincidence.

344
00:27:44,659 --> 00:27:46,540
Who are you calling? You seem so happy.

345
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:50,139
The man who loves me the most in this world.

346
00:27:51,550 --> 00:27:54,140
<i>[...]</i>

347
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:57,860
Give it back!

348
00:27:57,860 --> 00:28:00,700
Put his photo down!

349
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,480
Xu Huai Shi!

350
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:06,360
I've noticed that you're
getting more and more violent.

351
00:28:07,180 --> 00:28:08,720
I only looked at Li Shi Can's photo.

352
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:11,179
It's not like looking at him
will ruin his career.

353
00:28:11,980 --> 00:28:13,219
Say that again!

354
00:28:13,219 --> 00:28:16,220
I think you just have too much pocket money.

355
00:28:16,220 --> 00:28:19,340
Well, as for me, I've always had good luck with money.

356
00:28:19,340 --> 00:28:22,100
Just as I ran out of pocket money,

357
00:28:22,100 --> 00:28:24,860
someone offered to treat me to dinner.

358
00:28:24,860 --> 00:28:28,179
- Who?
- My Bro Song.

359
00:28:28,179 --> 00:28:32,160
A handsome guy who's second only to Shi Can. Handsome and loaded.

360
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:36,086
Most importantly, he spends money on me.

361
00:28:45,219 --> 00:28:47,039
Bro Song!

362
00:28:47,739 --> 00:28:50,739
What was I thinking? I have to go back again.

363
00:28:56,540 --> 00:28:58,699
What's Shi up to?

364
00:28:59,620 --> 00:29:02,780
So you're Bro Song. Who said you could call her Shi?

365
00:29:02,780 --> 00:29:07,179
Don't throw your age around and take advantage of her.

366
00:29:07,179 --> 00:29:09,660
Are you her classmate?

367
00:29:09,660 --> 00:29:12,180
We're ride-or-die.

368
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:13,620
Not just classmates.

369
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:16,480
Not just classmates? Then what else are you?

370
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:19,200
None of your business.

371
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:23,080
You want to know more about her, so you're trying to pump me for info?

372
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,860
No way.

373
00:29:24,860 --> 00:29:27,719
Didn't Shi tell you who I am?

374
00:29:27,719 --> 00:29:29,860
You?

375
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:32,179
Aren't you just that

376
00:29:32,179 --> 00:29:37,140
handsome and loaded guy
who's willing to spend money on her?

377
00:29:37,140 --> 00:29:39,720
Is that really how Shi talks about me?

378
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:42,620
It's just money. Who doesn't have that?

379
00:29:42,620 --> 00:29:44,480
Let me tell you,

380
00:29:45,660 --> 00:29:49,533
if you have any more bad intentions toward Xu Huai Shi,

381
00:29:50,459 --> 00:29:53,080
- I won't let you off easy!
- Song.

382
00:29:54,219 --> 00:29:56,310
You're still here?

383
00:29:57,060 --> 00:29:59,459
This is the classmate I mentioned, Zhao Yi.

384
00:29:59,459 --> 00:30:01,895
You've already met, right?

385
00:30:01,895 --> 00:30:03,939
So you're Zhao Yi.

386
00:30:03,939 --> 00:30:06,679
Not only have we met, I also know that you two

387
00:30:06,679 --> 00:30:09,080
are more than just classmates.

388
00:30:10,740 --> 00:30:12,600
Zhao Yi!

389
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:17,380
What nonsense did you say to Bro Song?

390
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:22,340
Shouldn't Bro Song's surname be Song?

391
00:30:23,153 --> 00:30:24,640
Then what about Sis Shi?

392
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:28,679
Xu Huai Song is my own brother. Got a problem with that?

393
00:30:29,780 --> 00:30:32,519
No problem, Bro Xu.

394
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:37,240
Bro Xu.

395
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:40,359
I have work to do tonight, so I can't have dinner with you.

396
00:30:46,219 --> 00:30:48,699
Mr. Liu, your friend has arrived. I'll show you the way.

397
00:30:48,699 --> 00:30:50,580
Sure, thanks.

398
00:31:11,540 --> 00:31:14,359
Didn't you go to Su City?

399
00:31:14,359 --> 00:31:16,920
You're back so soon.

400
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:27,800
<i>Shouldn't Bro Song's surname be Song?</i>

401
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:29,617
<i>Is our Lawyer Liu serious this time?</i>

402
00:31:29,617 --> 00:31:32,560
<i>This suit is very expensive. I've never seen him wear it since he bought it.</i>

403
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:35,220
<i>Who is it? Who is it? Do I know this lady?</i>

404
00:31:35,220 --> 00:31:37,420
<i>It's the one suing for defamation, Ms. Ruan.</i>

405
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:39,780
<i>Lawyer Liu drafted the contract.
He must seal it tonight.</i>

406
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:43,579
<i>Seal the deal on the contract, or seal the deal with the lady?</i>

407
00:32:14,380 --> 00:32:17,480
If I go with Zhikun Law Firm

408
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:20,980
would you be my lawyer, Lawyer Liu?

409
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:25,030
Yes, me.

410
00:32:25,793 --> 00:32:28,939
So we will proceed according to the plan we discussed on the phone, right?

411
00:32:28,939 --> 00:32:30,400
Of course.

412
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:32,739
We will provide legal advice
at the appropriate time,

413
00:32:32,739 --> 00:32:35,466
but will never go against the client's wishes.

414
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:39,920
That's great! I trust your professionalism, Lawyer Liu.

415
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:42,599
Then let's get the contract signed right away.

416
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:45,400
So soon?

417
00:32:50,700 --> 00:32:52,300
No rush.

418
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:56,220
It's fine if the contract
is delayed a few days.

419
00:32:56,220 --> 00:33:01,140
As for the online backlash, a few days won't make a big difference.

420
00:33:01,140 --> 00:33:02,659
Right, Lawyer Liu?

421
00:33:02,659 --> 00:33:04,780
How is that not a big difference?

422
00:33:04,780 --> 00:33:06,980
No! This can't be delayed.

423
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:10,460
Every extra day the backlash grows,
the more risk we take on.

424
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:12,659
Ruan Yu. Read the contract carefully.

425
00:33:12,659 --> 00:33:15,039
If you have any questions, ask me now. Don't hold back.

426
00:33:15,039 --> 00:33:17,219
I've already signed both copies.

427
00:33:17,219 --> 00:33:18,720
Okay!

428
00:33:22,780 --> 00:33:24,746
I don't have any questions.

429
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:31,640
Great!

430
00:33:32,639 --> 00:33:36,720
Lawyer Liu, for the lawsuit,
what materials do I need to prepare?

431
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:39,600
The top priority is to get the key records of defamation against you

432
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:44,080
from the online platforms to the notary office
for preservation of evidence.

433
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:45,580
I'll help you with that.

434
00:33:45,580 --> 00:33:49,779
Also, don't disclose your intention
to sue for now, to avoid tipping them off.

435
00:33:49,779 --> 00:33:52,260
- As for the rest--
- Hold on.

436
00:33:53,060 --> 00:33:56,160
I thought you were my lawyer, Lawyer Liu?

437
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:58,500
Lawyer Xu.

438
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:00,620
Are you going to be involved too?

439
00:34:00,620 --> 00:34:02,700
Lawyer Liu will appear in court.

440
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:04,940
I will assist in preparing the case.

441
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:11,640
But I can't afford to pay the retainer fees
for two lawyers at once.

442
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:13,979
Don't worry about that. He's doing it for practice.

443
00:34:13,979 --> 00:34:17,119
No need to pay him. And between you and me?

444
00:34:17,119 --> 00:34:19,080
I can give you a 20% discount.

445
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,299
Thank you, Lawyer Liu.

446
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:28,319
Actually, I've got contacts in the industry with copyright disputes.

447
00:34:28,319 --> 00:34:31,846
Maybe Lawyer Xu could
gain some experience there.

448
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,580
I'm fine with it.

449
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:39,240
What about Lawyer Liu?

450
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:55,459
After all,
those aren't Zhikun Law Firm's cases.

451
00:34:55,459 --> 00:35:01,220
So if Lawyer Xu gets involved, it might not look good within the firm.

452
00:35:04,139 --> 00:35:05,960
Right?

453
00:35:10,660 --> 00:35:12,220
Lawyer Xu.

454
00:35:12,220 --> 00:35:15,640
My understanding of you
assisting in preparing the case

455
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:20,560
is that you'll help Lawyer Liu with the strategy, not take over the whole--

456
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:25,019
The first step of preparation is to fully understand the case.

457
00:35:25,019 --> 00:35:29,860
So you have to read all the materials, including the entire novel.

458
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:36,380
Ms. Ruan, is there anything in your novel that is inconvenient to disclose?

459
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:40,361
No, not at all.

460
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:43,413
No.

461
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:46,273
Okay, the contract is signed.

462
00:35:46,273 --> 00:35:50,660
I'll start a work group chat to facilitate our communication going forward.

463
00:35:50,660 --> 00:35:52,380
Okay?

464
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:54,146
Okay.

465
00:36:02,419 --> 00:36:06,640
<i>In one kilometer, you will enter the airport expressway.</i>

466
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:13,380
<i>[...]</i>

467
00:36:15,010 --> 00:36:16,980
<i>[...]</i>

468
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:27,133
[Ruan Yu]
[Send]

469
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:32,210
[Notice: The user's privacy settings
don't allow adding via group chat.]

470
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:37,090
[Notice: The user's privacy settings
don't allow adding via group chat.]

471
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:57,520
<i>In our case, the part about organizing the plot will be handled by Lawyer Xu.</i>

472
00:36:57,520 --> 00:37:01,039
<i>If you have any questions, feel free to ask him anytime.</i>

473
00:37:06,019 --> 00:37:10,940
<i>Lawyer Liu, for the plot organization part, can I just work directly with you on it?</i>

474
00:37:12,260 --> 00:37:16,200
<i>For counter-plagiarism comparison, Lawyer Xu is more experienced.</i>

475
00:37:20,506 --> 00:37:22,760
<i>I just feel that Lawyer Xu is abroad, different time zone.</i>

476
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:26,819
<i>It's too inconvenient. Plus, he's probably pretty busy.</i>

477
00:37:26,819 --> 00:37:29,780
<i>Don't worry about it. He's a night owl.</i>

478
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:31,419
<i>And no matter how busy he is,</i>

479
00:37:31,419 --> 00:37:34,899
<i>he'll have to do me a favor and squeeze in time for this case.</i>

480
00:37:34,899 --> 00:37:38,219
<i>Once the materials are ready, just share them in the group.</i>

481
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:45,080
[Clues Related to Su Cheng. pdf]

482
00:37:46,346 --> 00:37:48,320
[@xhs]

483
00:37:59,580 --> 00:38:01,141
Hello?

484
00:38:03,099 --> 00:38:04,579
<i>Buddy.</i>

485
00:38:04,579 --> 00:38:07,780
<i>This type of case is your specialty, right?</i>

486
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:11,220
<i>You asked me to say in the group that you'd be handling this case.</i>

487
00:38:11,220 --> 00:38:14,140
<i>I did as you asked. But when Ruan Yu spoke up,</i>

488
00:38:14,140 --> 00:38:17,879
<i>you just played dead. What's that about?</i>

489
00:38:17,879 --> 00:38:21,200
<i>If you keep this up,
it makes things very awkward for me.</i>

490
00:38:27,546 --> 00:38:30,960
If you really feel uncomfortable being stuck in the middle,

491
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,993
why don't you move over here?

492
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:36,400
<i>Fine.</i>

493
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:43,340
You can tell her to add me on WeChat directly.

494
00:38:43,340 --> 00:38:45,039
<i>I've figured it out.</i>

495
00:38:45,039 --> 00:38:49,279
<i>So you suddenly came back just for Ruan Yu.</i>

496
00:38:50,579 --> 00:38:52,340
Shi got into some trouble.

497
00:38:52,340 --> 00:38:55,460
<i>What a lame excuse. For real?</i>

498
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:59,660
Instead of gossiping here, why not just have the client
contact me directly.

499
00:38:59,660 --> 00:39:01,220
<i>Hold on.</i>

500
00:39:01,220 --> 00:39:04,153
<i>Why are you making her reach out to you?</i>

501
00:39:05,579 --> 00:39:08,860
<i>Don't tell me you tried to add her, but she didn't accept.</i>

502
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:11,340
Nonsense.

503
00:39:11,340 --> 00:39:13,566
<i>So I guessed right.</i>

504
00:39:16,419 --> 00:39:21,260
Looks like when it comes to being rejected, Lawyer Liu is more experienced than me.

505
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:25,979
<i>Are you done? If so, I'm hanging up.</i>

506
00:39:25,979 --> 00:39:28,200
I haven't hung up yet!

507
00:39:31,979 --> 00:39:34,280
I'm more experienced than you at everything.

